        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. The child must have a genetically confirmed diagnosis of PWS;

          2. CY-BOCS Compulsion Score â‰¥ 8. The Compulsion Scale Score is being used as youth with
             PWS may have difficulty understanding or identifying the connection between
             obsessional thoughts and subsequent rituals. Therefore, use of the Total Score may
             provide an inaccurate depiction of symptoms (Storch et al., 2005);

          3. Stable on any psychotropic medications for 8 weeks prior to study entry;

          4. Between the ages of 6 and 17 years as the present measures are valid for use in this
             age span;

          5. At least one parent available to accompany the child to all sessions; and

          6. English speaking.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Current suicidal intent or risk;

          2. A positive diagnosis in the caregiver of mental retardation, psychosis, or other
             psychiatric conditions that would limit their ability to understand psychotherapy.
